Fig. 24
). Frontal vitta narrowing towards vertex, about twice pedicel width at lowermost level and subequal to pedicel width at uppermost level (
Fig 23
). Two pairs of proclinate fronto-orbital setae on upper half, and one reclinate pair before ocellar triangle. Ocellar triangle recognizable, broad and notably protuberant, with dense weak setulae, and bearing no ocelli (
Figs 23–24
). Fronto-orbital plate broad, about 2.5 x pedicel width at lowermost level (
Fig. 23
