Fig. 24
). In profile, anteroventral margin of head (bearing vibrissal, subvibrissal and subcranial setae/setulae) not subparallel to anteroventral margin of eye, closer to eye margin at vibrissal level (anteriorly) and diverging ventrally toward gena (posteriorly), becoming conspicuously distant (
Fig. 24
). Antenna inserted clearly above mid height of head in frontal view, and slightly above mid height of eye (
Fig. 24
